Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 2,545,589.48  
  Total Revenue = 5,565,589.48  
• Calculation:
  Gross Profit Margin = (2,545,589.48 ÷ 5,565,589.48) × 100 ≈ 45.74%

Step 2: Calculate Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities
• From the cash flow and balance sheet:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -81,548.37  
  Total Current Liabilities = 728,279.50  
• Calculation:
  Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = -81,548.37 ÷ 728,279.50 ≈ -0.112 or approximately -0.11

Thus, the answer is provided below.
